name: I only want to fly.
description:
You see, future traveler, I want you to understand that my point of view is sometimes blind: I just want to fly.

When I speak to you, I do so with confidence and I want it to be clear, I communicate what my needs have led me to. I burn myself when I reach the extreme, in those cases, I am not thinking responsibly but ¡How much hurt everything that we cannot change!

It frustrates what exceeds us, doesn't it?

The biggest discussion, I think, is whether we are going to keep flying to collect food or to enjoy spreading our wings, and doesn't matter where we go. Fate, bastard whoever sold it to us. May the infinite destinies rot! They have all left us behind once we have reached them.

The flight you've been on since you were born is the only one that hasn't left you. Is it possible that existence is suffering? I just want to feel that I fly.
